"Audiofiles and slides from the 6.5 hour long talk Nart Villeneuve and Ethan Zuckermann
gave on circumvention, anonymity and anonymous publishing are available
on Phillipine Center for Investigative Journalism's site"


An example of the type of fine points made in this very practical seminar:

"There's an assumption many people make that using a tool hosted
in the US (Yahoo mail, for instance) is "safer" than using a tool hosted
in China, for instance. As we've found out, this - unfortunately - isn't
true. In these workshops, we try to explain to users the various
vulnerabilities that come from being traceable back to an IP address,
and the strategies one can use for disguising that IP address. For users
who need to blog anonymously, we advocate for a solution that includes
Tor or a trusted third-party proxy, and Hushmail, which are used to
access Wordpress.com." (Ethan Zuckermann)